</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F3827FA6FFFD1A2CFF05CF724EECFEF7" box="[199,1417,259,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="567" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="BB272C2DFFFD1A2CFF05CF724EECFEF7" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,285]" box="[199,1417,259,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="567">
<emphasis id="89ECF03FFFFD1A2CFF05CF724A2BFEF7" bold="true" box="[199,334,259,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="567">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin “ 
<emphasis id="89ECF03FFFFD1A2CFDD2CF7249EDFEF6" box="[528,648,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="567">jacto-tatus</emphasis>
” meaning boasting, bragging; make gestures, display ostentatiously.
</paragraph>
